{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/background-information/definition/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"bbb9e2c5-c538-5f62-a833-9b160d36c0bf","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 58e2f6b7-60a7-4bbc-8912-56e1bb8b8350 --><h2>What is it?</h2><!-- end field 58e2f6b7-60a7-4bbc-8912-56e1bb8b8350 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 676ada4c-74de-487f-9d3b-2062d7dae0a8 --><!-- begin field 6d4943fa-7ce4-47cc-a02a-c20b36863626 --><ul><li>Travellers' diarrhoea is defined as passing three or more unformed stools in a 24 hour period with at least one additional symptom, such as abdominal pain or cramps, nausea, vomiting, fever, or blood in the stools [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">CATMAT, 2015</a>]. It occurs during, or within 10 days of, a trip abroad (usually to a less resource-rich destination) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Barrett, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Giddings et al, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Barrett and Brown, 2018</a>]. <ul><li>Stool passage in healthy young children can vary, so in this group, travellers' diarrhoea is defined by some authors as a two-fold or more increase in the frequency of unformed stools following overseas travel [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Ashkenazi et al, 2016</a>]. </li></ul></li><li>Travellers' diarrhoea can be described as [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">CDC, 2017a</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Riddle, 2017</a>]:  <ul><li><strong>Mild</strong> (acute) when it is tolerable, not distressing, and does not interfere with planned activities.</li><li><strong>Moderate</strong> (acute) when it is distressing or interferes with planned activities.</li><li><strong>Severe</strong> (acute) when it is incapacitating or completely prevents planned activities. Note that all dysentery (passage of bloody stools) is considered severe.</li></ul></li></ul><p> </p><!-- end field 6d4943fa-7ce4-47cc-a02a-c20b36863626 --><!-- end item 676ada4c-74de-487f-9d3b-2062d7dae0a8 -->","topic":{"id":"d5cf1db6-a6d9-54fb-b393-095d8af57067","topicId":"9042b194-f66e-44c6-a91c-76ffa626e3e8","topicName":"Diarrhoea - prevention and advice for travellers","slug":"diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers","lastRevised":"Last revised in February 2019","chapters":[{"id":"3f7bee04-88e6-5a40-86d5-e39dc29e4059","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"47ddb819-f046-5e92-999c-a3d47a00ede8","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"bdd3d81e-da2b-5807-b257-8dd4d73a596c","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"5ac4ad9d-b3fb-51c6-84de-19181b30e02c","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"5568a30c-164d-5d4f-8d41-ad7eff1173cb","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6f04e901-40c5-5906-a7eb-5935a99758bb","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"e0f32109-cb0a-51e3-aa59-bcac4a364a5f","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"4a74f052-b6c8-5743-b69f-30ffc630174e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"81c4309